"```sql\nSELECT \n    t.CustomerID, \n    AVG(t.Price / t.Amount) AS AveragePricePerItem, \n    c.Currency\nFROM \n    transactions_1k t\nJOIN \n    customers c ON t.CustomerID = c.CustomerID\nGROUP BY \n    t.CustomerID, c.Currency\nORDER BY \n    SUM(t.Amount * t.Price) DESC\nLIMIT 1;\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the top spending customer by summing the total transaction amounts and prices, then orders the results to find the highest spender. It also calculates the average price per single item purchased by dividing the total price by the total amount for each transaction. The currency used by the customer is retrieved from the `customers` table."